Base of anal fin moderately long. Anal-fin origin located distinctly posterior of middle of SL and approximately at middle of TL.Anal-fin margin nearly straight in most examined specimens, but convex in presumed mature males as evidenced by their distinct filamentous first rays of dorsal and pectoral fins (
Fig. 6
). Posterior most anal-fin ray with slight, membranous attachment to body.

Pectoral-fin length, excluding distal filament on first ray in mature males, approximately two-thirds of HL. Pectoral-fin margin distinctly convex with middle ray longest. First pectoral-fin ray spinous with smooth margins; spinous portion of ray short with length slightly more than one-half that of first branched ray, prolonged as filament in some, presumably male, specimens (
Fig. 6
).

